    <h3><br></h3>
    <h1>The Orders Militant of the Adeptus Sororitas</h1>
    <p>By Sister Regina-Benedetta of the Dialogus Order of the Quill<br><br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In the sepulcher of battle, the Orders Militant of the Adeptus Sororitas are the God-Emperors holiest warriors. In the glorious rapture of crusades, where saints are made and faith burns brightest, they are His will made manifest. They are the protectors of the faith and the bringers of purification. These ancient orders, their culture, and their history will be catalogued here for those scholars of history who love and fear the God Emperor of Man.</p>
    <p><a name="1"></a></p>
    <h3 style="text-align: center;">I<a name="1">: The</a> Reign of Blood</h3>
    <p style="margin-left: 20px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;When the Imperial Creed was established as the one true Religion of the Imperium, the Adeptus Ministorum, the Holy Mother Church, prosecuted great wars of faith to annihilate the remaining heretics and apostates that did not follow His true word. The innumerable armies and glorious might of the Holy Mother Church led to the Ecclesiarch of the Adeptus Ministorum to be given a seat as a High Lord of Holy Terra. In M.36, the craven Ecclesiarch Goge Vandire also usurped the seat belonging to the Administratum through usery, assassination, and subterfuge. The time of Vandire&apos;s brutal regime and resulting wars have since been dubbed the Reign of Blood or Age of Apostasy. <a name="2"></a></p>
    <h3 style="text-align: center;"><a name="2">II:</a> The Daughters of the Emperor</h3>
    <p style="margin-left: 20px;"><a name="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;All</a> orders of the Adeptus Sororitas who currently exist in the modern day can trace their history back to the Daughters of the Emperor, an order of spiritual warriors on an isolated world that is now the shrine world of San Leor. These Sisters, separate from the rest of the Imperium knew that the God-Emperor was God, and anointed Him above all. They learned the arts of war, and purged themselves of earthly corruption and desire. The warriors, pure of heart, were deceived by the fallen Ecclesiarch. Upon being exposed to unknown technology, they were fooled into believe Vandire was empowered by the God Emperor Himself.<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; The daughters of the Emperor, led by the blessed Alicia Dominica were instated as the personal guard of Vandire, and used as his instrument of retribution towards any who would slight him. The daughters of the Emperor were re-established by Vandire to be the Brides of the Emperor. These holy warriors were made to debase themselves as simple servants for the apostate. They waited on him, cooked and cleaned, and even coerced into other, carnal services. Yet, the Sisters continued their unwavering defense of Vandire, believing it was the God-Emperor&apos;s will.<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; Vandire&apos;s reign was soon opposed by Saint Sebastian Thor, the Fabricator-General of Mars, and the finest warriors of the God-Emperor the Adeptus Astartes. The now Brides of the Emperor held steadfast against the forces of the Imperial Fist, Fire Hawks, Soul Drinkers, and the Black Templars. The battle had come to a stalemate.<br><br><a name="3"></a></p>
    <h3 style="text-align: center;"><a name="3">III: The</a> Matriarchs and the End of Vandire</h3>
    <div style="margin-left: 20px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; The Adeptus Custodes, the personal guards of the God-Emperor of Man, sent a detachment to Vandire&apos;s Ecclesiarchal palace. The leader of this group, a centurion of the Companions, appealed to the Blessed Saint Alecia Dominica, and her five bodyguards. The Sisters at her side were Mina, Katherine, Arabella, Lucia, and Sylvana. These six became known as the Matriarchs of the Orders Majoris of the Adeptus Sororitas. Still serving the apostate Vandire, Saint Mina fought the Centurion alone, coming to blows for over an hour. Eventually, the Centurion was able to convince the soon to be matriarchs to leave the other Custodians as hostages, and follow him to the Imperial Palace. He had permitted them to learn of their betreyal from the God Emperor Himself.<br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; The Matriarchs entered the Imperial Palace and entered the throne room. What happened that day in that room is not known, but when the Blessed Matriarchs left, their hair was turned stark white, and their eyes filled with unquenchable bloodthirst. They renounced their name of Brides of the Emperor, once again becoming His daughters. Alicia Dominica confronted the apostate with her sisters by herside, her words and deeds are inscribed on her sarcophagus.<br><br></div>
    <p style="text-align: center;"><em>&quot;You have committed the ultimate Heresy. Not only have you turned your back on the Emperor and stepped from His light,<br>you have profaned His name and almost destroyed everything He has striven to build.<br>You have perverted and twisted the path He has laid for man to tread.<br>As your own decrees have stated, there can be no mercy for such a crime, no pity for such a criminal.<br>I renounce your lordship; you walk in the darkness and cannot be alllowed to live.<br>Your sentence has been long overdue and now it is time for you to die&quot;</em><br><br><br></p>
    <p style="margin-left: 20px;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The same Rosarius he had used to fool the Sisters at San Leor miraculously failed him only moments before Alicia Dominica&apos;s power sword met the heretic&apos;s neck. Sebastian Thor was declared the new Ecclesiarch, and the decree passive was made, banning any men at arms from fighting for the Adeptus Ministorum. Since there was still a need for protectors of the faith, the Daughters of the Emperor, who were not <strong><em>men</em></strong> at arms were reorganized into the Orders Militant of the Adeptus Sororitas. Half of these orders make up the Convent Prioris on Holy Terra and the other half the Convent Sanctorum on shrine world of Ophelia VII.</p>
    <div style="margin-left: 20px;"><br><a name="4">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">IV: The Order of the Ebon Chalice</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The
        </a> Order of the Ebon Chalice of the Convent Prioris on Holy Terra, founded by Saint Alicia Dominica, is the oldest of all the Orders of the Adeptus Sororitas. Their regalia is that of the Daughters of the Emperor. After the martyrdom of their matriarch, they strived to achieve the perfection of Saint Alicia Dominica, who was unquestionably the most worthy of His champions. They are charged with keeping one of the greatest relics of the Orders, the Holy Grail of Ages for which the order is named. Few know about the grail, but it is known that the Matriarch-Saint weilded it into battle, and when she spilled the contents, all could hear the voice of the God-Emperor of Man. Psykers were set ablaze, heretics eviscerated by the glorious sound of His voice. Single words shattered entire legions. <br><br><a name="5">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">V: The Order of the Sacred Rose</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The
        </a> Order of the Sacred Rose of the Convent Prioris on Holy Terra was founded in M.38 by the Ecclesiarch Deacis VI in honor of their Matriarch, Saint Arabella &quot;The Liberator&quot;. Saint Arabella was well known for her serenity and grace in the face of adversity. The Order of the Sacred Rose strives to embody her by being the calm eye of a deady maelstrom. The Order of the Sacred Rose are known as the finest tacticians of the orders militant, approaching every conflict with a grace and fluidity unmatched by any but the Adeptus Astartes. They, like all orders, are charged with the keeping of a relic. Theirs is the Light of Saint Agnathea, which is a adamantium brazier inscribed with the words and deeds of Saint Arabella. It guides the Sisters of the order through the darkness of the enemy, it&apos;s holy light charring the flesh of any of the impure who walk in it&apos;s radiance.<br><br><a name="6">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">VI: The Order of the Argent Shroud</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The
        </a> Order of the Argent Shroud of the Convent Prioris on Holy Terra was founded in M.36 by the Ecclesiarch and successor of the Saint Sebastian Thor, Alexis XXII in honor of their Matriarch, Saint Silvana. Saint Silvana, known for her few words and many deeds became the model for her Order. There are no recorded words in any Ecclesiarchal records spoken by Silvana from the time she was born until the time she was martyred by servants of the archenemy. As such, the sisters of her order fight in silence and silence their enemies. After battles, they solemnly collect the corpses of their martyrs, preparing them, and returning them to their stations in a week or less, though none know what becomes of their fallen within the walls of their sanctuaries. <br><br>The order is named after the relic of Saint Silvana, specifically her burial shroud which is all that remains after her undecaying body was mysteriously stolen. The Sisters of her order bring this shroud into battle, where the visage of Saint Silvana miraculously appears upon the cloth.<br><a name="7">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">VII: The Order of Our Martyred Lady</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The
        </a> Order of our Martyred Lady of the Convent Sanctorum on Ophelia VII, formerly the Order of the Fiery Heart, was founded in M.36 by Ecclesiarch and successor of Saint Sebastian Thor, Alexis XXII after the Martyrdom of Saint Katherine. After her death, her order was renamed The Order of Our Martyred Lady. The Order of our Martyred Lady is likely one of, if not the most famous of the Orders Militant, being the order of the Revered Lady and Living Saint Celestine as well as the order of the Living Saint Sabbat, for whom the Sabbat Worlds are named. The Order of Our Martyred Lady are some of the most devout servants of the God-Emperor, and some of His most effective. They have proven themselves in many Holy Wars and Crusades throughout the history of the Imperium. They strive to meet a glorious end like their Matriarch. Each fallen sister only instills greater zeal in the sisters of the order, and there is no greater reward to them than death in service to the God-Emperor. <br><br>The Order&apos;s greatest relic is the inturred body of Saint Katherine, known as her Triumph. However, the Revered Lady Saint Celestene has taken up the arms and armor of Saint Katherine as her own, smiting any who oppose Him on innumerable worlds in an unknowable number of hopeless battles where she appears at the direst hour. <br><br><a name="8">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">VIII: The Order of the Valorous Heart</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The
        </a> Order of the Valorous Heart of the Convent Sanctorum on Ophelia VII was founded in M.36 by Ecclesiarch Alexis XXII. It was meant to act as the immoveable anvil for the hammer that was Katherine&apos;s Order of the Fiery Heart. Their sanctuaries stand in the most wretched reaches of the Imperium, besieged by xenos hoardes or deep within the poisonous swamps of death worlds. Their Matriarch is Saint Lucia, the youngest of the Matriarchs. The Saint was martyred, her eyes gouged as her sisters were tortured. Not wanting to bring more pain to their now blind Matriarch, the sisters were silent in their pain. They meditated on it as they were martyred. Now, all sisters of the order strive to feel the unthinkable pain their Matriarch once did, and bare it in silence. They are known for refusing pain medication, for self flaggelating, and even going as far as self-mutilation. For them, pain is the crucible that purifies the soul.<br><br><a name="9">
            <h3 style="text-align: center;">IX: The Order of the Bloody Rose</h3>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The
        </a> Order of the Bloody Rose of the Convent Sanctorum on Ophelia VII was founded in M.38 by Ecclesiarch Deacis VI in honor of Saint Mina, who embodied the God-Emperor&apos;s hatred for His enemies. Her order is inspired by her martyrdom, her body having been found in a chamber with many dead heretics, adorned with the viscera of her enemies. The Bloody Rose are the fiercest fighters of the Adeptus Sororitas, taking up the evisceator and relishing the mayhem of melee combat. They scream their prayers and litanies in almost inhuman, shrieking voices as they cut down the enemies of the faith, only stopping their justified slaughter when there is no heretic blood left to spill. They are the bloody executioners of the Adeptus Sororita and know the past of least evil is lies with the swift destruction of His enemies.<a name="10">
            <h3><br></h3>
        </a><a name="11"></a></div>
